article.headline: Toledo 107, Indiana-Northwest 43
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Matt Smith scored 21 points and Julius Brown 20 to lead Toledo over Indiana-Northwest 107-43 on Tuesday night, for the Rockets' fifth largest margin of victory. The 64-point win is Toledo's largest since defeating Defiance 97-29 on Dec. 5, 1943. The Rockets, whose highest score was 136 points against Hillsdale in 1968, put up their most points since going for 108 against Grand Valley State on Nov. 16, 1998. Rian Pearson added 19 points and 13 rebounds, and Dominique Buckley had 15 points for Toledo, which snapped a three-game skid. The Rockets were 39 of 71 from the field (54.9 percent), while going 21 of 25 from the free-throw line (21 of 25), and held the RedHawks to 24.5 percent shooting (12 of 49). Justin Latimore scored 17 points and Baile Barnett had 10 to lead the RedHawks, of the NAIA, who counted the game as an exhibition.
